    <string name="settings_title">Settings</string>
    <string name="settings_how_header">How BurnPony works</string>
    <string name="settings_how_body">Notes are encrypted on this device with AES-256-GCM before anything is uploaded. The decryption key travels only in the part of the link after the #, which browsers never send to any server. An optional passphrase is stretched with PBKDF2 and mixed into the key. The server stores ciphertext it cannot read, plus a note ID, view count, and expiry. No accounts, no names, no analytics.</string>
    <string name="settings_limits_body">Honest limits: whoever has the full link (and passphrase, if set) can read the note. A recipient can always copy or photograph a note while it is visible. Self-destruction limits future access; it does not control the moment of reading.</string>
    <string name="settings_selfhost_header">Self-hosting (advanced)</string>
    <string name="settings_selfhost_footer">The whole server is open source and runs on any shared PHP host. Point this at your own instance and BurnPony never talks to ours. Notes remember which server they were created on.</string>
